/FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=132.topic><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Reply</FONT></A></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Death of a Weevil</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">As part of my mule renovation plan, Ghar travelled to Mayoi last night to tell Weevil that his services were no longer required. As was to be expected, Weevil didn't handle being downsized very well. Despite having been stripped of all his equipment except for his beloved bright red fez, he was determined to see the dires once before he retired.<br>
<br>
So, naked except for a loincloth and his fez, he headed for the South Dires Portal in the mountains near Mayoi. By some miracle, he made it to the portal without being ripped apart by bloodthirsty rabbits, only to find that it was camped by a herd of Bronze Armordillos. Undaunted, he bellowed his war cry (&quot;Eeeeeeek!!!&quot;) in a high-pitched shriek, and charged for the portal. He made it to the portal just ahead of the dillos' snapping jaws, only to be greeted with the message &quot;You are not powerful enough to enter this portal&quot;.<br>
<br>
The next thing he saw was the lifestone, and just before he faded into oblivion forever, he heard a disembodied voice utter the last words he would ever hear:<br>
<br>
&quot;You have lost your fez.&quot; <br>
<br>
